description:
As part of the judiciary system in ancient Israel, the land was appointed six cities of refuge. If someone was falsely or unjustly accused, they would flee to one of these cities to be protected in a safe haven. The parallels between them and our relationship with Jesus and what he does for us is something we all should know.
